gomodel:SYNGO_4802  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099059 replaced by GO:0048787" , "Rationale: Figure 1B and movie S4: superresolution microscopy (3D-STORM) showed that Ryk colocalized with both presynaptic marker Bassoon and postsynaptic marker PSD-95. Signal for this antibody is much weaker than other proteins shown in this figure, but the images and movie shown in S4 together are suggestive of the model proposed by authors in Figure 1C.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected. As also depicted by authors in Figure 1C.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampi were dissected from E18.5 mice, and hippocampal neuron culture was performed as previously described\"\n\nantibody:\nmouse anti-Ryk (generated in the Zou laboratory)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4802" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

